* satranc http://www.chess.com/chessmentor/view_lesson?id=1686
This is a roughly even endgame in which White has an extra pawn. In many positions, this pawn would be insufficient for a win, but here White has a few advantages. White's pawn provides a useful shield for White's king which allows both White pieces to occupy active squares rather than defend against possible checks. Black, on the other hand, must be careful, as White may have some useful checks against the exposed king.
---------------------------------------------------------
White's extra pawn at e2 does not play an active role in the game, but it is a good defender of the White king. White's knight at g5 is attacked by the Black queen. How can White best meet this nuisance?
** Hint1: Sometimes giving is better than taking in chess.
** Hint2: Your knight wants to move forward, but all good squares are currently protected.
** Hint3: You always want to look at possible captures, no matter how strange they look at first.
In tactical combinations, it is often hardest to find the first move, but when you have recognized or found a pattern, you will be able to find the final position quickly. With more practice, you will begin to see more and more patterns in your games, adding to your positional understanding.
